headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored five of his 27 points in the final 2:28 to lead the Houston Rockets to a 101-99 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alperen Sengun scores 27 to lead Rockets to 101-99 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 31 points, 12 rebounds and six assists and the Boston Celtics rallied in the second half to beat the slumping Milwaukee Bucks 113-107 on Sunday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 23 in second half to rally Celtics to a 113-107 victory over slumping Bucks

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored a career-high 38 points, including a career-best seven 3-pointers, and Tyrese Haliburton added 35 points and 14 assists to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 132-121 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathurin, Haliburton power Indiana Pacers to 132-121 win over New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 23 points and seven assists, Goga Bitadze added 10 points and 12 rebounds and the Orlando Magic pulled away in the second half to a 121-94 win over the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Wizards 121-94 for second straight blowout win without Paolo Banchero

headlines.description: — Jared McCain had a career-high 27 points as the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a five-game losing streak with a 107-105 overtime win over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jared McCain and Guerschon Yabusele lead the 76ers to 107-105 OT win over the Hornets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jovic made the tying layup and go-ahead foul shot with 7.8 seconds left to send the Miami Heat past the Minnesota Timberwolves 95-94...
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat edge Timberwolves 95-94 on Nikola Jovic's layup-and-1 with 7.8 seconds left

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 36 points, and the Golden State Warriors held off a late rally to defeat the Oklahoma City Thunder 127-116 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 36, OKC loses Holmgren to hip injury in Warriors' 127-116 win over Thunder

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. hit a mid-range jumper with seven seconds left and the Denver Nuggets won their fifth straight, 122-120 over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michael Porter Jr. hits winning jumper in the final seconds and Denver beats Dallas 122-120

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers
Toronto Raptors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James recorded his second straight triple-double, and Anthony Davis scored 22 points before leaving with an eye injury in the third quarter of the Los Angeles Lakers ' 123-103 victory...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron gets 2nd straight triple-double, Anthony Davis injured in Lakers' 123-103 win over Raptors
